Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.65,0:00:18.12,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Welcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.11,0:00:20.80,Default,,0,0,0,,This year, we are delighted to
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.80,0:00:22.90,Default,,0,0,0,,introduce a new framework in iOS
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.90,0:00:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,11 called Core NFC, that would
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.76,0:00:27.95,Default,,0,0,0,,allow your apps to integrate NFC
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.95,0:00:30.47,Default,,0,0,0,,on iPhone 7 and iPhone 7 Plus.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.61,0:00:34.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Using Core NFC, apps can
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.22,0:00:35.49,Default,,0,0,0,,interact with their physical
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.49,0:00:37.08,Default,,0,0,0,,environment and the real-world
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.08,0:00:38.05,Default,,0,0,0,,objects within it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.76,0:00:41.06,Default,,0,0,0,,You may already know that Apple
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.17,0:00:43.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Pay uses NFC for complex
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.77,0:00:44.38,Default,,0,0,0,,payment.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.38,0:00:46.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, with the introduction of
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.55,0:00:49.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Core NFC, you will be able to
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.66,0:00:52.72,Default,,0,0,0,,use NFC in your applications to
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.72,0:00:54.58,Default,,0,0,0,,create new and innovative user
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.58,0:00:58.68,Default,,0,0,0,,experiences with the iPhone.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.12,0:01:00.69,Default,,0,0,0,,In this session, we will give
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.69,0:01:02.44,Default,,0,0,0,,you a brief overview of new
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.44,0:01:04.48,Default,,0,0,0,,field communications, what is
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.48,0:01:06.58,Default,,0,0,0,,supported in the Core NFC
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.58,0:01:08.92,Default,,0,0,0,,framework, the requirements and
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.92,0:01:11.24,Default,,0,0,0,,details for using it, and some
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.24,0:01:12.10,Default,,0,0,0,,example code.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.71,0:01:16.06,Default,,0,0,0,,To start off, let's talk a
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.06,0:01:17.62,Default,,0,0,0,,little bit about Near Field
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.62,0:01:18.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Communication.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.67,0:01:22.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Near Field Communication, known
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.74,0:01:25.69,Default,,0,0,0,,simply as NFC, is a wireless
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.69,0:01:27.13,Default,,0,0,0,,technology that allows the
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.13,0:01:28.93,Default,,0,0,0,,exchange of information between
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.93,0:01:30.58,Default,,0,0,0,,devices that are within close
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.61,0:01:31.28,Default,,0,0,0,,proximity.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.98,0:01:33.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Limited to a range of just a few
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.99,0:01:34.80,Default,,0,0,0,,centimeters.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.71,0:01:38.37,Default,,0,0,0,,NFC is actually a collection of
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.41,0:01:39.94,Default,,0,0,0,,a number of different standards
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.94,0:01:40.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and protocols.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.51,0:01:43.70,Default,,0,0,0,,All of these standards coexist
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.70,0:01:45.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and are used in different
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.07,0:01:45.90,Default,,0,0,0,,applications.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.90,0:01:48.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You may have seen or had
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.32,0:01:50.16,Default,,0,0,0,,experience with NFC text.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.67,0:01:51.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The small little stickers or
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.93,0:01:53.71,Default,,0,0,0,,cards which can be read
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.09,0:01:56.07,Default,,0,0,0,,wirelessly by an NFC reader.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.72,0:01:59.40,Default,,0,0,0,,NFC text comes in a wide variety
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.40,0:02:01.33,Default,,0,0,0,,of shapes, sizes, and
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.33,0:02:02.06,Default,,0,0,0,,capacities.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.92,0:02:04.50,Default,,0,0,0,,They are classified into five
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.54,0:02:06.29,Default,,0,0,0,,categories, known as Type 1
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.54,0:02:07.31,Default,,0,0,0,,through Type 5.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.18,0:02:09.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Each one corresponding to a
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.64,0:02:10.47,Default,,0,0,0,,different standard.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.38,0:02:13.90,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, Type 3 texts are
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.90,0:02:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,based on FEDECA [assumed
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.72,0:02:17.26,Default,,0,0,0,,spelling] and Type 4 is based on
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.56,0:02:21.49,Default,,0,0,0,,ISO-14443.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.49,0:02:23.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The NFC Forum has defined the
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.86,0:02:26.58,Default,,0,0,0,,NFC Data Exchange Format, or
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.67,0:02:28.73,Default,,0,0,0,,NDEF for short, as a common
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.73,0:02:30.53,Default,,0,0,0,,messaging format for exchanging
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.53,0:02:32.65,Default,,0,0,0,,data in a standardized way among
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.65,0:02:34.36,Default,,0,0,0,,the different text types.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.59,0:02:38.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Now that we have covered some
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.04,0:02:40.59,Default,,0,0,0,,NFC basics, let's take a look at
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.59,0:02:43.09,Default,,0,0,0,,what you can do with Core NFC.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.68,0:02:47.02,Default,,0,0,0,,For the initial launch of Core
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.08,0:02:49.63,Default,,0,0,0,,NFC, we have focused on NFC Tag
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.63,0:02:51.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Reading, which can be used to
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.15,0:02:52.89,Default,,0,0,0,,enhance the user experience in a
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.89,0:02:54.52,Default,,0,0,0,,wide variety of ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.69,0:02:57.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Potential applications include
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.20,0:03:01.61,Default,,0,0,0,,connecting user to location or
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.61,0:03:03.59,Default,,0,0,0,,context-specific content,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.69,0:03:06.03,Default,,0,0,0,,connecting physical hardware
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.03,0:03:09.09,Default,,0,0,0,,with your application, and even
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.09,0:03:10.67,Default,,0,0,0,,for in-store product information
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.67,0:03:11.89,Default,,0,0,0,,or inventory tracking.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.78,0:03:15.31,Default,,0,0,0,,In addition, NFC Tags can be
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.31,0:03:17.21,Default,,0,0,0,,used in place of QR codes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.21,0:03:21.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Core NFC will allow your
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.88,0:03:23.69,Default,,0,0,0,,application to read any NDEF
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.69,0:03:24.63,Default,,0,0,0,,formatted tag.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.50,0:03:27.07,Default,,0,0,0,,This greatly simplifies the
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.07,0:03:28.59,Default,,0,0,0,,process of reading tags within
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.59,0:03:30.06,Default,,0,0,0,,your application or for having
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.06,0:03:31.20,Default,,0,0,0,,to deal with the different
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.20,0:03:31.94,Default,,0,0,0,,standards.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.87,0:03:34.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Tag reading is supported on
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.50,0:03:36.42,Default,,0,0,0,,iPhone 7 and iPhone 7 Plus.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.59,0:03:39.81,Default,,0,0,0,,At this time, Core NFC does not
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.81,0:03:41.58,Default,,0,0,0,,support writing or formatting
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.58,0:03:42.41,Default,,0,0,0,,operations.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.92,0:03:46.89,Default,,0,0,0,,There are two requirements for
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.89,0:03:48.39,Default,,0,0,0,,using Core NFC in your
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.39,0:03:49.62,Default,,0,0,0,,application.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.90,0:03:53.82,Default,,0,0,0,,First, Core NFC is an
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.82,0:03:54.97,Default,,0,0,0,,entitlement-protective
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.97,0:03:55.49,Default,,0,0,0,,framework.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.42,0:03:58.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You will need to turn on the
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.22,0:04:00.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Near Field Communication Tag
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.12,0:04:02.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Reading Capability from Xcode to
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.41,0:04:03.48,Default,,0,0,0,,get this entitlement.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.79,0:04:05.86,Default,,0,0,0,,However, this capability would
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.86,0:04:07.43,Default,,0,0,0,,not be in Xcode for the first
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.43,0:04:09.22,Default,,0,0,0,,[inaudible] released at WWDC.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.22,0:04:11.97,Default,,0,0,0,,In the meantime, you can
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.97,0:04:13.33,Default,,0,0,0,,manually request this
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.33,0:04:14.76,Default,,0,0,0,,entitlement by visiting the
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.76,0:04:17.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Certificates, Identifiers and
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.02,0:04:19.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Profiles page on the Apple
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.19,0:04:20.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Developer website.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.92,0:04:25.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The second requirement for Core
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.83,0:04:28.06,Default,,0,0,0,,NFC is a Scan Usage Description.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.35,0:04:30.98,Default,,0,0,0,,This string is required in your
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.98,0:04:33.02,Default,,0,0,0,,application's info P-list file,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.35,0:04:34.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and it will be displayed to the
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.79,0:04:36.13,Default,,0,0,0,,user when your application
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.13,0:04:38.43,Default,,0,0,0,,starts NFC scanning.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.39,0:04:40.72,Default,,0,0,0,,For more information, you can
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.72,0:04:43.99,Default,,0,0,0,,watch the WWDC session, Privacy
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.08,0:04:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and Your Apps.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.53,0:04:49.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Now that you have configured
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.66,0:04:51.67,Default,,0,0,0,,your project correctly, let's
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.67,0:04:53.07,Default,,0,0,0,,review some additional details
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.07,0:04:54.85,Default,,0,0,0,,about tag reading with the Core
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.85,0:04:55.71,Default,,0,0,0,,NFC framework.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.45,0:05:00.86,Default,,0,0,0,,First, tag reading is an
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.86,0:05:02.92,Default,,0,0,0,,on-demand process, meaning that
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.92,0:05:04.66,Default,,0,0,0,,your application has to initiate
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.66,0:05:06.50,Default,,0,0,0,,a tag reading activity using a
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.50,0:05:06.99,Default,,0,0,0,,session.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.02,0:05:11.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Second, your application has to
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.09,0:05:12.91,Default,,0,0,0,,be visible and foregrounded in
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.91,0:05:14.44,Default,,0,0,0,,order to start a tag reading
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.44,0:05:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,activity.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.36,0:05:17.10,Default,,0,0,0,,A tag reading session will be
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.10,0:05:18.60,Default,,0,0,0,,ended if your application is
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.60,0:05:20.15,Default,,0,0,0,,backgrounded or ceases to be
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.15,0:05:20.57,Default,,0,0,0,,visible.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.47,0:05:24.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Next, each tag reading activity
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.60,0:05:26.33,Default,,0,0,0,,is limited to 60 seconds at a
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.33,0:05:26.75,Default,,0,0,0,,time.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.99,0:05:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,If a session has timed out or
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.96,0:05:30.59,Default,,0,0,0,,invalidated, your application
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.59,0:05:31.94,Default,,0,0,0,,must create a new session to
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.94,0:05:33.65,Default,,0,0,0,,initiate another tag reading
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.65,0:05:34.21,Default,,0,0,0,,activity.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.74,0:05:38.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You can configure a session to
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.25,0:05:40.10,Default,,0,0,0,,read either a single tag or
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.10,0:05:41.13,Default,,0,0,0,,multiple tags.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.62,0:05:43.60,Default,,0,0,0,,In a single tag reading mode,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.51,0:05:45.52,Default,,0,0,0,,the session will be ended
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.52,0:05:47.32,Default,,0,0,0,,automatically after a tag is
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.32,0:05:47.68,Default,,0,0,0,,read.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.28,0:05:50.30,Default,,0,0,0,,On the other hand, a multi-tag
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.30,0:05:51.64,Default,,0,0,0,,reading session will remain
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.64,0:05:53.10,Default,,0,0,0,,active until canceled by the
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.10,0:05:54.97,Default,,0,0,0,,user, or the 60-second timeout
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.97,0:05:55.61,Default,,0,0,0,,is reached.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.25,0:06:00.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Finally, as mentioned
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.16,0:06:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,previously, the NFC Usage String
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.18,0:06:06.14,Default,,0,0,0,,defined in your info P-list will
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.14,0:06:07.71,Default,,0,0,0,,be displayed to the user while
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.71,0:06:09.17,Default,,0,0,0,,the tag reading activity is in
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.17,0:06:09.75,Default,,0,0,0,,progress.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.30,0:06:13.93,Default,,0,0,0,,We have provided a sample
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.93,0:06:15.13,Default,,0,0,0,,application along with this
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.13,0:06:16.44,Default,,0,0,0,,presentation to demonstrate the
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.44,0:06:19.13,Default,,0,0,0,,use of Core NFC.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.13,0:06:20.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Consider the case where you want
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.40,0:06:21.57,Default,,0,0,0,,to take a physical kind of
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.57,0:06:22.27,Default,,0,0,0,,inventory.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.72,0:06:24.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, we are showing you the key
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.67,0:06:26.45,Default,,0,0,0,,user interaction sequence of the
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.45,0:06:27.47,Default,,0,0,0,,sample application.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.80,0:06:29.94,Default,,0,0,0,,The sample application consists
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.94,0:06:31.81,Default,,0,0,0,,of a main table view, and a Scan
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.81,0:06:32.27,Default,,0,0,0,,button.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.85,0:06:34.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Every time an inventory item is
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.69,0:06:36.49,Default,,0,0,0,,scanned, it is displayed as a
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.49,0:06:38.09,Default,,0,0,0,,role entry in this main table
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.09,0:06:38.42,Default,,0,0,0,,view.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.19,0:06:40.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Just click on the Scan button to
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.91,0:06:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,start a tag scanning.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.04,0:06:46.82,Default,,0,0,0,,This UI will be presented to the
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.82,0:06:48.84,Default,,0,0,0,,user hopefully on top of your
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.84,0:06:50.84,Default,,0,0,0,,application once tag scanning
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.84,0:06:51.48,Default,,0,0,0,,has begun.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.64,0:06:54.41,Default,,0,0,0,,During tag scanning, the user's
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.41,0:06:56.08,Default,,0,0,0,,description string is displayed
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.08,0:06:56.99,Default,,0,0,0,,within the UI.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.99,0:06:59.50,Default,,0,0,0,,At any time, the user can hit
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.50,0:07:01.11,Default,,0,0,0,,the Cancel button to stop a tag
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.11,0:07:03.15,Default,,0,0,0,,scanning, which will invalidate
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.15,0:07:03.89,Default,,0,0,0,,the reader session.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.42,0:07:09.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The UI will get updated once an
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.15,0:07:11.12,Default,,0,0,0,,NFC tag has been successfully
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.12,0:07:11.48,Default,,0,0,0,,read.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.85,0:07:14.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, we have configured our
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.20,0:07:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,,reader session to be single tag
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.92,0:07:16.52,Default,,0,0,0,,read mode.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.79,0:07:22.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Finally, the overlaid UI will be
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.03,0:07:23.53,Default,,0,0,0,,dismissed, and the application
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.53,0:07:25.14,Default,,0,0,0,,will be foregrounded once the
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.28,0:07:26.89,Default,,0,0,0,,tag reading session has ended.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.36,0:07:30.97,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.11,0:07:32.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's walk through the code
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.14,0:07:33.15,Default,,0,0,0,,together from the sample
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.15,0:07:34.54,Default,,0,0,0,,application we have just shown.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.14,0:07:38.34,Default,,0,0,0,,At a high level, you would need
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.34,0:07:39.77,Default,,0,0,0,,to perform these three easy
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.77,0:07:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,steps to enable tag reading in
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.92,0:07:42.68,Default,,0,0,0,,your application.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.64,0:07:47.33,Default,,0,0,0,,First, adopt the NFC NDEF Reader
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.33,0:07:48.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Session Delegate Protocol.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.12,0:07:52.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Next, create an instance of the
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.60,0:07:54.63,Default,,0,0,0,,NFC NDEF Reader Session Class,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.97,0:07:56.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and provide it with your
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.55,0:07:57.07,Default,,0,0,0,,delegate.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.83,0:08:01.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Finally, start a reader session
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.09,0:08:02.51,Default,,0,0,0,,using the Begin method, and
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.51,0:08:04.12,Default,,0,0,0,,handle the delegate callbacks.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.69,0:08:09.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Here is a cool snippet from the
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.16,0:08:10.68,Default,,0,0,0,,sample application, illustrating
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.68,0:08:11.84,Default,,0,0,0,,the three-step approach.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.05,0:08:14.85,Default,,0,0,0,,To start off, we import the Core
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.85,0:08:16.99,Default,,0,0,0,,NFC framework into the code.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.46,0:08:22.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Here we adopt the delegate
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.39,0:08:23.71,Default,,0,0,0,,protocol in Table View
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.71,0:08:25.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Controller, which will handle
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.02,0:08:26.72,Default,,0,0,0,,the two required callbacks.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.74,0:08:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,They invalidate with error and
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.52,0:08:33.24,Default,,0,0,0,,detect NDEF.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.84,0:08:38.39,Default,,0,0,0,,The invalidate with error
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.39,0:08:39.99,Default,,0,0,0,,callback will notify your
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.99,0:08:41.49,Default,,0,0,0,,application when a tag reading
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.49,0:08:42.62,Default,,0,0,0,,activity has stopped.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.31,0:08:45.75,Default,,0,0,0,,This can happen for a variety of
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.79,0:08:46.33,Default,,0,0,0,,reasons.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.89,0:08:48.56,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, a tag has been
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.56,0:08:50.25,Default,,0,0,0,,successfully read in a single
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.25,0:08:51.12,Default,,0,0,0,,tag read session.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.06,0:08:53.54,Default,,0,0,0,,The user has chosen to stop the
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.54,0:08:54.70,Default,,0,0,0,,tag scanning activity.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.00,0:08:57.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The 3-second timeout has expired
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.65,0:09:00.06,Default,,0,0,0,,or the application is no longer
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.06,0:09:00.76,Default,,0,0,0,,in the foreground.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.53,0:09:03.77,Default,,0,0,0,,The specific session object
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.77,0:09:05.19,Default,,0,0,0,,provided in the first parameter
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.38,0:09:06.90,Default,,0,0,0,,will be invalidated after the
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.90,0:09:07.93,Default,,0,0,0,,function exits.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.30,0:09:10.28,Default,,0,0,0,,A new reader session instance is
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.28,0:09:12.15,Default,,0,0,0,,required for additional tag
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.15,0:09:12.45,Default,,0,0,0,,reading.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.40,0:09:17.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The detect NDEFs will be invoked
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.29,0:09:19.14,Default,,0,0,0,,every time an NDEF has been read
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.14,0:09:20.23,Default,,0,0,0,,from an NFC tag.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.43,0:09:22.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Your application can then grab
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.82,0:09:23.95,Default,,0,0,0,,the payload from the NDEF
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.95,0:09:26.71,Default,,0,0,0,,message, decode it, and handle
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.71,0:09:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the message as appropriate.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.75,0:09:33.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Finally, we have an extra method
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.85,0:09:35.24,Default,,0,0,0,,that links to the Scan button
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.24,0:09:36.74,Default,,0,0,0,,for starting a single tag read
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.74,0:09:37.23,Default,,0,0,0,,session.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.48,0:09:40.20,Default,,0,0,0,,All you need to do is create an
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.25,0:09:42.14,Default,,0,0,0,,instance of NFC NDEF Reader
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.14,0:09:43.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Session with your data gate,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.32,0:09:45.64,Default,,0,0,0,,then invoke to begin method to
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.64,0:09:46.78,Default,,0,0,0,,start tag scanning.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.29,0:09:48.93,Default,,0,0,0,,If you wish to create a
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.93,0:09:51.33,Default,,0,0,0,,multi-tag reading session, set
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.33,0:09:53.13,Default,,0,0,0,,the invalidate at the first read
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.19,0:09:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,parameter to False.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.74,0:09:56.61,Default,,0,0,0,,If you need to stop an ongoing
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.61,0:09:58.30,Default,,0,0,0,,session programmatically, you
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.30,0:09:59.89,Default,,0,0,0,,can call the invalidate method.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.07,0:10:02.12,Default,,0,0,0,,This will trigger your
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.19,0:10:04.10,Default,,0,0,0,,invalidate with error callback,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.58,0:10:05.48,Default,,0,0,0,,letting you know that the
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.48,0:10:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,session has ended.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.57,0:10:13.39,Default,,0,0,0,,In summary, it is very simple to
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.39,0:10:15.28,Default,,0,0,0,,enable NFC tag reading with Core
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.52,0:10:17.77,Default,,0,0,0,,NFC by following these steps.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.28,0:10:22.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Enable the NFC tag reading
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.12,0:10:22.85,Default,,0,0,0,,capability.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.39,0:10:26.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Make sure your Scan Usage
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.68,0:10:28.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Description String is set in
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.34,0:10:30.43,Default,,0,0,0,,your info P-list.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.12,0:10:33.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Integrate the Core NFC framework
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.91,0:10:34.57,Default,,0,0,0,,in your code.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.15,0:10:37.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And start reading tags.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.58,0:10:43.05,Default,,0,0,0,,For more information about this
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.05,0:10:44.64,Default,,0,0,0,,presentation and our sample
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.64,0:10:47.29,Default,,0,0,0,,code, please visit this online
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.95,0:10:48.09,Default,,0,0,0,,link.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.56,0:10:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, here are some related
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.44,0:10:52.74,Default,,0,0,0,,sessions you might be interested
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.74,0:10:52.98,Default,,0,0,0,,in.
